<s> Newport Electronics Inc. named a new slate of officers , a move that follows replacement of the company 's five incumbent directors last week . </s>
<s> Milton B. Hollander , 60 years old , was named chief executive officer , succeeding Barrett B. Weekes . </s>
<s> Mr. Hollander 's Stamford , Conn.-based High Technology Holding Co. acquired most of its 49.4 % stake in Newport in August . </s>
<s> Mr. Hollander was named chairman last week , succeeding Mr. Weekes , who was among the ousted directors . </s>
<s> The company has declined requests to discuss the changes , but Mr. Weekes has said that Mr. Hollander wanted to have his own team . </s>
<s> Scott Wakeman was named president and chief operating officer of U.S. operations , titles that had been held by Mr. Weekes . </s>
<s> Mr. Wakeman was vice president of the instrument and controls division of closely held Omega Engineering Inc. , another company controlled by Mr. Hollander . </s>
<s> A company spokesman did n't know Mr. Wakeman 's age . </s>
<s> James R. Lees , 51 , vice president of Newport 's European operations , was named executive vice president and chief operating officer of European operations , assuming some former duties of Mr. Weekes . </s>
<s> Arthur B. Crozier , 34 , an attorney , was named secretary , succeeding John Virtue , who was another of the ousted directors . </s>
